         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">9 August 1855 ¶  ¶ I have the honor to ackdge the rect ¶  of your dated "Brisbane July 1855" ¶   ¶  ¶ intimating the possibility of the "North Australian Expedition"— in which you have accepted an app...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">55.08.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From John Moore</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 1611, unit 1, pp. 339-40, VPRS 2814 outward registered correspondence, VA 856 Colonial Secretary's Office, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9 August 1855</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to ackdge the rect<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">acknowledge the receipt.</p>
               </note> of your dated "Brisbane July 1855"<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M to W. Haines, July 1855.</p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>intimating the possibility of the "North Australian Expedition"— in which you have accepted an appointment as Botanist — being longer absent than the period of eighteen months named in your former letter, and requesting that your leave of absence may, under such circumstances, be extended to the time of the return of the expedition.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am instructed in reply to acquaint you that H.E<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">His Excellency [Governor Hotham].</p>
               </note> has the greatest pleasure in conceding your request.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">(Signed) J Moore. ACS<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Assistant Colonial Secretary.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferdinand Mueller Esq</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Brisbane</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">New South Wales<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M left Sydney on 18 July 1855 and so probably did not receive this letter until after the expedition returned to Sydney in 1857.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
